@SalehHindi So i've been trying to load the package **html2canvas** in the Controls.jsx  

I imported the html2canvasExport from the html2canvas.js script that i got [here](https://github.com/niklasvh/html2canvas/releases/download/v0.5.0-beta4/html2canvas.js)

put it in a app folder in static/assets/dashboard/components, and did 

```
var H2C = require('./app/html2canvas.js');
//we will then use html2canvasExport, which is Exported from html2canvas.js

[... JSX code ...]

        <Button
          onClick={() => {
            H2C.html2canvasExport(document.body).then(function(canvas) {
              document.body.appendChild(canvas);
            });
          }}
        >
          <i className="fa fa-download" />
        </Button>

/*
Also tried this function :
          H2C.html2canvasExport( document.body,{
          onrendered: function(canvas) {
          window.open(canvas.toDataURL());
*/

```

The error I get in the console  is that H2C.html2canvasExport is not a function, so it seems that i'm not importing the function correctly, also tried with import {...} and import ...

Do you think it's a bad approach ?

Thanks for your help if you have some time to look at this
